1
00:02:24,912 --> 00:02:26,860
Your breakfast, Your Highness.

2
00:02:27,655 --> 00:02:29,467
What did I tell you to do?

3
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:34,756
Didn't I tell you about the white suit?

4
00:02:52,995 --> 00:02:55,356
Besides getting dressed up every day,

5
00:02:56,190 --> 00:02:58,636
can you be more useful?

6
00:03:14,779 --> 00:03:18,200
Get out! Get out! Get out!

7
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:21,139
Get out! Get out! Get out!

8
00:03:21,139 --> 00:03:22,894
You blood-sucking capitalist!

9
00:03:22,894 --> 00:03:24,563
Making profit out of our hardship.

10
00:03:24,563 --> 00:03:27,299
They stole our land, right?

11
00:03:27,299 --> 00:03:28,971
That's right!

12
00:03:28,971 --> 00:03:32,320
- Wish you a disastrous life!
- With a speedy way to hell!

13
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:33,456
Look at this,

14
00:03:33,456 --> 00:03:35,862
this is the grand opening
of Prince Rawikan's mall.

15
00:03:35,862 --> 00:03:37,776
And there is chaos already.

16
00:03:37,776 --> 00:03:39,813
Not surprising.

17
00:03:39,813 --> 00:03:43,616
Prince Rawikan Wongnaruenart is
a wealth hoarding capitalist.

18
00:03:43,616 --> 00:03:46,674
People in Phra Nakhon hate him so much.

19
00:03:49,896 --> 00:03:51,597
Why did you stop the car?

20
00:03:53,016 --> 00:03:54,408
No mall!

21
00:03:54,408 --> 00:03:55,683
No mall!

22
00:03:55,683 --> 00:03:58,342
- No mall!
- What should we do, Your Highness?

23
00:03:58,342 --> 00:03:59,824
No mall!

24
00:03:59,824 --> 00:04:01,270
No mall!

25
00:04:01,270 --> 00:04:04,596
Hey! The bloodsucker is here!

26
00:04:08,048 --> 00:04:09,936
- Stop it!
- Hey! Stop!

27
00:04:09,936 --> 00:04:13,195
- Go away!
- No mall! No mall!

28
00:04:13,195 --> 00:04:16,816
No mall! No mall!

29
00:04:16,816 --> 00:04:20,295
- Get out!
- No mall.

30
00:04:20,295 --> 00:04:21,888
Keep driving.

31
00:04:21,888 --> 00:04:24,294
If we keep going, we will hit them.

32
00:04:24,294 --> 00:04:26,116
I don't give a damn!

33
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:29,304
They are useless leeches.

34
00:04:29,304 --> 00:04:30,558
No mall!

35
00:04:30,558 --> 00:04:32,190
No mall!

36
00:04:32,190 --> 00:04:34,236
I told you to keep going!

37
00:04:48,056 --> 00:04:49,757
Stop taking photos.

38
00:04:50,936 --> 00:04:53,036
I told you to stop!

39
00:04:59,038 --> 00:05:00,739
Stop taking my picture already!

40
00:05:02,712 --> 00:05:06,116
I don't want to see my face
in your newspapers.

41
00:05:06,878 --> 00:05:08,168
I hope you know that

42
00:05:08,168 --> 00:05:12,051
I have enough power
to shut down your newspaper.

43
00:05:12,051 --> 00:05:13,752
Including all of you!

44
00:05:24,712 --> 00:05:26,413
Who threw it?

45
00:05:30,371 --> 00:05:32,296
Who threw it here?

46
00:05:32,296 --> 00:05:33,997
It's me.

47
00:05:40,720 --> 00:05:43,883
You son of a bitch! You took my house!

48
00:05:43,883 --> 00:05:45,822
I will curse you.

49
00:05:45,822 --> 00:05:48,104
I want you to face a horrific life.

50
00:05:48,104 --> 00:05:50,036
Just go to hell!

51
00:05:51,998 --> 00:05:54,019
Hey!

52
00:05:54,019 --> 00:05:55,876
Hey! He hurt an old man!

53
00:06:04,894 --> 00:06:06,595
Get him!

54
00:06:18,606 --> 00:06:20,307
Your Highness?

55
00:06:29,056 --> 00:06:34,414
- Get out!
- Get out!

56
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:43,640
[Naruenart Bank]

57
00:07:01,046 --> 00:07:03,152
They are all gone, Your Highness.

58
00:07:03,152 --> 00:07:04,934
But...

59
00:07:04,934 --> 00:07:06,635
But what?

60
00:07:07,438 --> 00:07:10,456
But you need to pay more compensation
for them.

61
00:07:14,323 --> 00:07:16,371
Why do I need to?

62
00:07:16,371 --> 00:07:18,436
I already paid off their compensation.

63
00:07:19,147 --> 00:07:22,235
It's true that you already paid them,

64
00:07:22,235 --> 00:07:25,366
but you didn't give them enough time
to find new places.

65
00:07:25,366 --> 00:07:27,696
To make it worse,
you sent someone to drive them away.

66
00:07:27,696 --> 00:07:32,667
Some of them lost their belongings,
or family members.

67
00:07:32,667 --> 00:07:35,052
It's normal for them to be furious like this.

68
00:07:37,227 --> 00:07:39,240
They keep asking for more and more.

69
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:41,116
They don't know when to stop asking.

70
00:07:45,091 --> 00:07:49,336
I heard what you said.
They just want more money.

71
00:07:49,336 --> 00:07:53,448
If you refuse to give them,
they could come back to harass you.

72
00:07:53,448 --> 00:07:57,086
That's why I hired your stupid faces
to be here.

73
00:07:57,086 --> 00:07:58,787
You need to handle the situation.

74
00:08:00,947 --> 00:08:03,996
If I need to pay them,

75
00:08:04,851 --> 00:08:07,276
I will deduct it from your salaries.

76
00:08:09,067 --> 00:08:11,156
Starting from you.

77
00:08:20,155 --> 00:08:22,726
Who is the head of security?

78
00:08:22,726 --> 00:08:24,676
It's me, Your Highness.

79
00:08:42,054 --> 00:08:44,358
Your Highness? Can you give us a few minutes?

80
00:08:44,358 --> 00:08:47,016
How are you going to handle this?

81
00:08:47,016 --> 00:08:48,891
Please let us know.

82
00:08:48,891 --> 00:08:51,531
What is your responsibility for this?

83
00:08:51,531 --> 00:08:52,902
Don't leave yet.

84
00:08:52,902 --> 00:08:54,636
Your Highness!

85
00:09:15,736 --> 00:09:17,437
Fai,

86
00:09:18,085 --> 00:09:21,550
you know the rules in our bandit community,
don't you?

87
00:09:21,550 --> 00:09:23,251
Of course.

88
00:09:32,702 --> 00:09:34,931
I told you that people from the inside
can't go out,

89
00:09:34,931 --> 00:09:36,806
and the outsiders can't get in.

90
00:09:39,166 --> 00:09:41,456
You remember that, don't you?

91
00:09:44,376 --> 00:09:46,718
I never forget that.

92
00:09:46,718 --> 00:09:49,946
These villagers must have wandered off.

93
00:09:56,696 --> 00:09:58,996
I will go out for robbery.

94
00:09:59,688 --> 00:10:02,147
While I am away,

95
00:10:02,147 --> 00:10:05,276
you can't let it happen again.

96
00:10:06,867 --> 00:10:08,796
Sure, I promise.

97
00:11:02,366 --> 00:11:03,880
Stop!

98
00:11:03,880 --> 00:11:05,181
You need to leave!

99
00:11:05,181 --> 00:11:06,667
Go back to where you came from!

100
00:11:06,667 --> 00:11:07,750
Who are you?

101
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:11,286
Wait! This village isn't like
other villages that you visited.

102
00:11:11,286 --> 00:11:12,816
They don't welcome the strangers.

103
00:11:12,816 --> 00:11:15,876
- Stop!
- We've come too far to go back, kiddo.

104
00:11:24,198 --> 00:11:26,356
Hey!

105
00:11:27,256 --> 00:11:30,176
You need to cover your eyes.

106
00:11:30,176 --> 00:11:31,996
Use that cloth to cover your eyes.

107
00:11:32,976 --> 00:11:34,677
Come on!

108
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:59,301
Fai!

109
00:12:00,198 --> 00:12:01,787
Fai!

110
00:12:01,787 --> 00:12:02,966
Fai, no!

111
00:12:02,966 --> 00:12:05,184
Nobody will make it out alive.

112
00:12:05,184 --> 00:12:06,747
He was just lost.

113
00:12:06,747 --> 00:12:09,076
He hasn't seen your faces.

114
00:12:10,939 --> 00:12:14,800
If we let him go,
and he tells the police on us,

115
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:17,723
we will be in so much trouble,
my dear Lukjan.

116
00:12:17,723 --> 00:12:19,916
We have to follow the rules.

117
00:12:20,694 --> 00:12:24,316
Fai, I beg you. Please let him go.

118
00:12:25,558 --> 00:12:27,339
Fine.

119
00:12:27,339 --> 00:12:30,276
This is on your account, Lukjan.

120
00:12:34,443 --> 00:12:37,716
Didn't you hear it? Go!

121
00:12:40,294 --> 00:12:41,995
Run! Fast!

122
00:14:17,115 --> 00:14:18,816
Deputy Mesa.

123
00:14:21,238 --> 00:14:22,216
What is it?

124
00:14:22,216 --> 00:14:24,182
We still haven't had any leads, sir.

125
00:14:24,182 --> 00:14:26,888
It seemed like Mai and Fai disappeared.

126
00:14:26,888 --> 00:14:29,150
They left us no trace.

127
00:14:29,150 --> 00:14:31,859
Tawan's case is even worse.

128
00:14:31,859 --> 00:14:35,070
Nobody has ever seen his face,
they've only heard his name.

129
00:14:35,070 --> 00:14:38,716
They said that Tawan is a well-known bandit
among other bandits.

130
00:14:46,816 --> 00:14:48,654
Keep on digging.

131
00:14:48,654 --> 00:14:50,062
Yes, sir.

132
00:15:22,558 --> 00:15:24,259
Have you been drinking?

133
00:15:26,846 --> 00:15:29,547
Yes, I have.

134
00:15:46,774 --> 00:15:52,196
I wonder if you've ever noticed
that you didn't pay attention to me.

135
00:15:53,334 --> 00:15:55,035
What are you trying to do?

136
00:15:59,920 --> 00:16:04,256
I'm trying what we both
should have been trying for so long.

137
00:16:11,987 --> 00:16:14,676
I will make this night

138
00:16:15,283 --> 00:16:19,116
so special for you, Your Highness.

139
00:16:21,715 --> 00:16:23,416
Phetpring, you need to stop.

140
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:27,676
Stop acting like a cheap woman by the road.

141
00:16:31,288 --> 00:16:33,076
I feel embarrassed for you.

142
00:16:38,589 --> 00:16:41,205
Why should I?

143
00:16:41,205 --> 00:16:46,116
You and I are husband and wife.

144
00:16:49,328 --> 00:16:51,844
It's because I don't love you, Phetpring.

145
00:16:52,976 --> 00:16:54,577
Don't you remember?

146
00:16:54,577 --> 00:16:58,116
We're results of an arranged marriage.

147
00:16:58,776 --> 00:17:03,866
We got married
because we have duties to fulfill.

148
00:17:03,866 --> 00:17:06,326
It's not because of love.

149
00:17:07,547 --> 00:17:12,916
And I will never sleep with a woman
that I don't fall in love with.

150
00:17:13,656 --> 00:17:16,436
- Keep that in mind.
- Your Highness?

151
00:17:20,976 --> 00:17:26,134
I agreed to marry you
because of our families' promises,

152
00:17:26,134 --> 00:17:29,256
that my father made with yours.

153
00:17:32,928 --> 00:17:37,036
I just don't want people to say that
my father wasn't a man of his word.

154
00:17:39,360 --> 00:17:42,076
One more thing,

155
00:17:43,115 --> 00:17:47,596
I have never desired someone like you.

156
00:18:24,198 --> 00:18:29,187
The sun is shining through your window
and you are still in bed.

157
00:18:29,187 --> 00:18:30,888
What's wrong?

158
00:18:34,184 --> 00:18:35,982
Now you're worrying about me?

159
00:18:35,982 --> 00:18:38,516
Just give me the number, how much?

160
00:18:39,192 --> 00:18:41,534
You're such a perfect daughter for me.

161
00:18:41,534 --> 00:18:43,768
You know me so well.

162
00:18:43,768 --> 00:18:46,756
Hey, give me 10,000.

163
00:18:47,496 --> 00:18:49,560
What? 10,000?

164
00:18:49,560 --> 00:18:51,288
I just gave you the money last week.

165
00:18:51,288 --> 00:18:53,646
You spend all of your money already?

166
00:18:53,646 --> 00:18:56,787
Pring, I am your mother.

167
00:18:56,787 --> 00:18:57,832
What's the matter?

168
00:18:57,832 --> 00:19:00,116
I can't ask you for another 10,000 baht?

169
00:19:00,116 --> 00:19:02,710
- Is it such a big trouble for you?
- Mom!

170
00:19:02,710 --> 00:19:04,470
I don't have that much money.

171
00:19:04,470 --> 00:19:07,782
The money that my husband gave me,
I already gave it all to you.

172
00:19:07,782 --> 00:19:10,436
Can you spend less money?

173
00:19:23,839 --> 00:19:25,382
Mom!

174
00:19:25,382 --> 00:19:27,083
Mom!

175
00:19:29,067 --> 00:19:30,206
Mom!

176
00:19:30,206 --> 00:19:31,907
Mom.

177
00:19:57,384 --> 00:19:59,726
Pring, honey?

178
00:19:59,726 --> 00:20:01,556
Can you hear me?

179
00:20:05,936 --> 00:20:08,195
Mom?

180
00:20:08,195 --> 00:20:11,515
What is going on with me?

181
00:20:11,515 --> 00:20:14,032
You fainted in your room.

182
00:20:14,032 --> 00:20:17,656
You were lucky someone saw you.

183
00:20:20,240 --> 00:20:21,941
Hello, doctor.

184
00:20:22,550 --> 00:20:24,075
I'm glad that you're here.

185
00:20:24,075 --> 00:20:27,902
Pring was unconscious for a minute,

186
00:20:27,902 --> 00:20:30,123
so I asked the doctor to come and see her.

187
00:20:30,123 --> 00:20:32,411
So what is wrong with my daughter-in-law?

188
00:20:32,411 --> 00:20:34,396
Is it something really bad?

189
00:20:35,627 --> 00:20:39,264
Her condition isn't a bad sign,

190
00:20:39,264 --> 00:20:41,956
but it is something to be celebrated.

191
00:20:46,262 --> 00:20:49,116
I'm happy for you, Your Highness.

192
00:20:49,739 --> 00:20:51,676
About what?

193
00:20:53,288 --> 00:20:56,356
Ms. Pring is eight weeks pregnant now.

194
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:21,136
Pring? I'm about to be a grandma?

195
00:21:21,136 --> 00:21:23,443
Pring, how are you feeling?

196
00:21:23,443 --> 00:21:24,707
Oh my goodness!

197
00:21:24,707 --> 00:21:27,336
Thank you so much, honey.
You should lie down.

198
00:21:27,336 --> 00:21:29,598
Just lie down, okay?

199
00:21:29,598 --> 00:21:31,299
Oh my goodness!

200
00:21:32,086 --> 00:21:34,416
How are you feeling? Still having a headache?

201
00:21:34,416 --> 00:21:35,515
Not anymore.

202
00:21:35,515 --> 00:21:37,216
No?

203
00:21:57,038 --> 00:21:59,043
What you asked me to investigate,

204
00:21:59,043 --> 00:22:01,356
I have a report on that.

205
00:22:27,635 --> 00:22:29,406
Pring, honey.

206
00:22:29,406 --> 00:22:32,816
Lady Sakolwan told me that you're pregnant.

207
00:22:32,816 --> 00:22:36,636
Thank you for making my dream come true.

208
00:22:40,248 --> 00:22:41,656
You know what?

209
00:22:41,656 --> 00:22:44,902
Carrying a baby from Wongnaruenart

210
00:22:44,902 --> 00:22:47,316
is like carrying a big treasure.

211
00:22:48,056 --> 00:22:53,280
It means that
the family's enormous wealth and properties

212
00:22:53,280 --> 00:22:55,636
will belong to us.

213
00:23:00,208 --> 00:23:03,316
What's wrong? What's with the face?

214
00:23:04,120 --> 00:23:08,579
Having a baby with Prince Rawikan
is something to celebrate.

215
00:23:08,579 --> 00:23:13,396
Also, it can stop the rumor
that you two sleep in separate rooms.

216
00:23:16,363 --> 00:23:20,759
Mom, you need to listen to me carefully.

217
00:23:23,958 --> 00:23:25,756
The rumor...

218
00:23:27,176 --> 00:23:29,917
isn't just a rumor, but it's a fact.

219
00:23:29,917 --> 00:23:32,397
I've been married to him for two years

220
00:23:32,397 --> 00:23:37,094
but we have never slept together
as a husband and wife, not once.

221
00:23:37,094 --> 00:23:38,795
But...

222
00:23:40,246 --> 00:23:43,836
But... If you didn't sleep together,

223
00:23:44,502 --> 00:23:46,276
how did you get pregnant?

224
00:23:51,520 --> 00:23:53,221
Pring!

225
00:23:54,107 --> 00:23:56,636
- Mom!
- Come here, right now.

226
00:23:59,990 --> 00:24:02,376
Did you cheat on your husband?

227
00:24:02,376 --> 00:24:05,196
Tell me who your lover is, tell me!

228
00:24:08,136 --> 00:24:10,070
You ungrateful bitch!

229
00:24:10,070 --> 00:24:12,747
Why are you aiming for something low?

230
00:24:12,747 --> 00:24:17,206
Your husband is a prince,
and you still slept with a guy with no title?

231
00:24:17,206 --> 00:24:20,435
Mom! I'm sorry, I'm so sorry.

232
00:24:20,435 --> 00:24:23,219
I'm mortified enough,
I don't know what to do.

233
00:24:23,219 --> 00:24:25,123
I'm scared.

234
00:24:25,123 --> 00:24:26,659
- Mom!
- Stop talking.

235
00:24:26,659 --> 00:24:28,483
Why can't you be patient?

236
00:24:28,483 --> 00:24:31,096
He has never looked at me.

237
00:24:31,096 --> 00:24:32,136
You know it well

238
00:24:32,136 --> 00:24:35,128
how hurtful a woman can be
when her husband doesn't care about her.

239
00:24:35,128 --> 00:24:37,480
Why didn't you use any protection?

240
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:39,596
How did you let yourself get pregnant?

241
00:24:42,792 --> 00:24:46,611
You have to do whatever it takes
to stop him from divorcing you.

242
00:24:46,611 --> 00:24:48,556
What you have to do...

243
00:24:49,612 --> 00:24:55,016
is to keep me as a mother-in-law
of Prince Rawikan Wongnaruenart.

244
00:24:55,016 --> 00:24:56,717
You hear me?

245
00:25:35,718 --> 00:25:39,715
I don't think that it is necessary
for you to go by yourself.

246
00:25:39,715 --> 00:25:41,939
You can let someone else attend.

247
00:25:41,939 --> 00:25:44,419
Pring is pregnant,

248
00:25:44,419 --> 00:25:46,796
I think she wants to be around her husband.

249
00:25:47,699 --> 00:25:49,651
I really have to go there, Mom.

250
00:25:49,651 --> 00:25:53,203
It is the grand opening
of our first bank in the northeast.

251
00:25:53,203 --> 00:25:55,215
I want to take care of it myself.

252
00:26:04,611 --> 00:26:09,050
Can I hug you goodbye?

253
00:26:17,683 --> 00:26:20,230
This will be the last time

254
00:26:20,230 --> 00:26:24,076
that the two of us see each other.

255
00:26:26,619 --> 00:26:29,019
Have a safe trip, honey.

256
00:26:29,019 --> 00:26:31,843
I will see you this evening.

257
00:26:31,843 --> 00:26:33,544
See you later.

258
00:27:12,446 --> 00:27:13,496
What's wrong?

259
00:27:13,496 --> 00:27:16,542
A car broke down in front of us.

260
00:27:16,542 --> 00:27:19,276
Please wait for me in the car, Your Highness.

261
00:27:30,992 --> 00:27:32,693
Ake!

262
00:28:53,814 --> 00:28:55,516
Who sent you?

263
00:28:57,456 --> 00:28:59,157
Who are you?

264
00:30:34,779 --> 00:30:36,236
Follow him!

265
00:30:50,200 --> 00:30:51,901
Come here!

266
00:34:06,944 --> 00:34:08,444
Hey!

267
00:34:24,160 --> 00:34:26,920
[Love, Piangjan]

268
00:34:30,251 --> 00:34:31,952
Hey!

269
00:34:34,838 --> 00:34:36,539
Hey!

270
00:34:44,022 --> 00:34:45,056
What is going on?

271
00:34:45,056 --> 00:34:47,516
Stop asking me questions and help me.

272
00:34:51,341 --> 00:34:53,491
Lukjan? Is this your blood?

273
00:34:53,491 --> 00:34:56,516
Not mine, it is his.

274
00:35:26,885 --> 00:35:28,586
No more fever.

275
00:35:46,144 --> 00:35:48,299
Calm down, I'm here to help.

276
00:35:48,299 --> 00:35:49,936
Hey, you!

277
00:35:49,936 --> 00:35:51,996
Hey!

278
00:35:52,741 --> 00:35:54,442
Hey!

279
00:35:55,750 --> 00:35:57,939
Hey!

280
00:35:57,939 --> 00:35:59,676
Please calm down.

281
00:36:08,099 --> 00:36:09,631
Hey!

282
00:36:12,659 --> 00:36:14,360
Who am I?

283
00:36:36,085 --> 00:36:39,448
The man whom you helped
doesn't remember anything.

284
00:36:39,448 --> 00:36:42,543
He doesn't remember who he is,
or where he comes from.

285
00:36:44,589 --> 00:36:45,928
Oh my goodness, I see death coming.

286
00:36:45,928 --> 00:36:47,464
He's not dead.

287
00:36:47,464 --> 00:36:49,040
He just suffered from amnesia.

288
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:50,832
I meant us.

289
00:36:50,832 --> 00:36:52,768
We're dead for real.

290
00:36:52,768 --> 00:36:55,984
You know about the rules pretty well.

291
00:36:55,984 --> 00:36:59,016
People from the inside can't go out,
and the outsiders can't come in.

292
00:36:59,016 --> 00:37:02,051
The villagers could see this guy right here.

293
00:37:02,051 --> 00:37:06,076
If it's not him, then it is us who will die.

294
00:37:09,156 --> 00:37:12,000
The only way to cure him

295
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:14,592
is to get him out of Prai Island
as fast as possible.

296
00:37:14,592 --> 00:37:18,411
More importantly,
nobody must see you get him out.

297
00:37:18,411 --> 00:37:21,827
We need to restore his memories back first.

298
00:37:21,827 --> 00:37:27,582
What is your plan
to keep hm away from the villagers?

299
00:37:27,582 --> 00:37:31,796
Don't you know that
they have eyes and ears everywhere?

300
00:37:33,622 --> 00:37:36,128
Let me take care of that matter.

301
00:37:36,128 --> 00:37:42,276
Your job is to get his memories back
as soon as possible.

302
00:37:56,979 --> 00:38:00,036
Hey, you look good in it.

303
00:38:01,116 --> 00:38:03,236
Come on, have a seat.

304
00:38:03,928 --> 00:38:05,752
I think it looks weird on me.

305
00:38:05,752 --> 00:38:09,416
Not weird at all, you look cool.

306
00:38:09,416 --> 00:38:11,315
Cool and stylish. Right, Dad?

307
00:38:11,315 --> 00:38:12,787
Have a seat.

308
00:38:12,787 --> 00:38:14,488
Let me see.

309
00:38:16,576 --> 00:38:19,347
I forgot to introduce ourselves.
This is my dad. He is a doctor.

310
00:38:19,347 --> 00:38:21,956
He will heal you.

311
00:38:25,083 --> 00:38:27,350
Take off your top.

312
00:38:27,350 --> 00:38:28,807
Why would I?

313
00:38:29,635 --> 00:38:33,688
If you don't take it off,
how would I know where your wounds are?

314
00:38:33,688 --> 00:38:35,389
Take it off.

315
00:38:36,147 --> 00:38:38,096
Don't be shy.

316
00:38:38,096 --> 00:38:41,406
I've seen a lot of this.

317
00:38:41,406 --> 00:38:42,880
- Come on, let me help.
- Hey!

318
00:38:42,880 --> 00:38:45,126
Hey! Come on, don't do it.

319
00:38:45,126 --> 00:38:47,174
- Hey! It's fine.
- Let me help you.

320
00:38:47,174 --> 00:38:48,603
Can you do it properly?

321
00:38:48,603 --> 00:38:51,059
It's like you're wrestling with a guy.

322
00:38:51,059 --> 00:38:52,760
Dad! Come on!

323
00:39:03,475 --> 00:39:05,064
You need to stop, Lukjan.

324
00:39:05,064 --> 00:39:06,830
Get out! That's enough.

325
00:39:06,830 --> 00:39:08,916
You need to wait outside.

326
00:39:17,251 --> 00:39:18,645
Take it off.

327
00:39:48,968 --> 00:39:52,156
What are you doing?
Why are you here by yourself?

328
00:39:52,776 --> 00:39:55,552
I have something for you, Tiew.

329
00:39:55,552 --> 00:39:57,253
Something for me?

330
00:40:01,212 --> 00:40:02,913
Here, take it.

331
00:40:13,469 --> 00:40:15,856
Did you see what's inside the ring?

332
00:40:15,856 --> 00:40:17,557
Inside the ring?

333
00:40:21,440 --> 00:40:23,120
[Love, Piangjan]

334
00:40:23,400 --> 00:40:25,056
- Hey!
- What ring is this?

335
00:40:25,056 --> 00:40:26,176
Give it to me.

336
00:40:26,176 --> 00:40:28,336
- Give it back to me.
- No, I won't.

337
00:40:28,336 --> 00:40:31,476
Why are you so possessive of it?
Why is it so important to you?

338
00:40:36,742 --> 00:40:38,102
Give it to me.

339
00:40:38,102 --> 00:40:40,516
"Love, Piangjan".

340
00:40:42,538 --> 00:40:44,436
This ring?

341
00:40:45,237 --> 00:40:47,236
The one that you gave to Tiew?

342
00:40:48,496 --> 00:40:50,197
That's right.

343
00:40:50,938 --> 00:40:53,156
How did it end up here with you?

344
00:40:53,781 --> 00:40:57,116
Or... Tiew is back?

345
00:41:15,291 --> 00:41:17,574
Your wound on your head looks better.

346
00:41:17,574 --> 00:41:20,699
And I only see your wounds externally.

347
00:41:20,699 --> 00:41:24,476
No broken or cracked bones.

348
00:41:29,584 --> 00:41:32,107
Are you sure that you checked me thoroughly?

349
00:41:32,107 --> 00:41:33,876
Of course, I am sure.

350
00:41:37,787 --> 00:41:39,318
Why's that?

351
00:41:39,318 --> 00:41:41,232
You judged me from my look?

352
00:41:41,232 --> 00:41:44,956
You think that I'm a nobody
and claiming to be a doctor, don't you?

353
00:41:57,171 --> 00:41:58,872
That's right.

354
00:42:00,088 --> 00:42:02,436
If I had known
that you had such a filthy mouth,

355
00:42:03,075 --> 00:42:05,856
I wouldn't have risked my life to safe you.

356
00:42:05,856 --> 00:42:07,676
Why did you need to risk your life?

357
00:42:08,360 --> 00:42:10,096
Don't mind me. I just said this and that.

358
00:42:10,096 --> 00:42:14,956
You had a concussion,
so your memories are lost.

359
00:42:17,093 --> 00:42:21,036
But the memories can be restored.

360
00:42:21,995 --> 00:42:24,169
When?

361
00:42:24,169 --> 00:42:27,416
It would take days for some.

362
00:42:27,416 --> 00:42:32,037
While some could take months, or even years.

363
00:42:41,814 --> 00:42:46,296
It means that you will help restore
memories of a man that you saved

364
00:42:46,296 --> 00:42:48,814
so you would find out what happened to Tiew?

365
00:42:48,814 --> 00:42:54,256
Why did the ring that you gave to Tiew
show up with him?

366
00:42:54,256 --> 00:42:55,957
That's right.

367
00:42:57,078 --> 00:43:00,592
He is the only one
who can give me all of these answers.

368
00:43:00,592 --> 00:43:05,334
I have a job to protect
and take the best care of him.

369
00:43:05,334 --> 00:43:07,240
You know it well.

370
00:43:07,240 --> 00:43:10,236
This is not an easy joy for you, Lukjan.

371
00:43:12,436 --> 00:43:13,795
I know.

372
00:43:13,795 --> 00:43:17,678
I want you to keep it confidential.

373
00:43:17,678 --> 00:43:23,476
Don't let anyone on Prai Island know
that I have a stranger in my house.

374
00:43:36,576 --> 00:43:38,956
Our guys found a dead body this morning.

375
00:43:39,608 --> 00:43:43,283
I searched him
and I found handcuffs and a gun.

376
00:43:43,283 --> 00:43:45,096
I think he was a police officer.

377
00:43:45,096 --> 00:43:46,995
We should leave his body right here.

378
00:43:46,995 --> 00:43:48,611
I don't want us to be in trouble.

379
00:43:48,611 --> 00:43:50,595
Don't be such a coward.

380
00:43:50,595 --> 00:43:52,931
Why are you so scared of a dead body?

381
00:43:52,931 --> 00:43:58,438
We need to fear
if there is someone else in our village.

382
00:44:11,560 --> 00:44:13,776
Look at this blood.

383
00:44:13,776 --> 00:44:16,296
It's like what I expected.

384
00:44:16,296 --> 00:44:20,716
Besides this police officer,
there is someone else.

385
00:44:23,027 --> 00:44:25,396
They must have wandered into our village.

386
00:44:27,216 --> 00:44:29,120
You need to alert Mai about this.

387
00:44:29,120 --> 00:44:31,197
Tell him to come back as fast as he can.

388
00:44:32,121 --> 00:44:35,701
We will search every one and find them.

389
00:44:35,701 --> 00:44:38,332
Got it. Come on, let's go.

390
00:44:57,907 --> 00:44:59,406
Come here.

391
00:44:59,406 --> 00:45:01,107
Hey! Come here.

392
00:45:03,547 --> 00:45:06,246
I saw a dead body at the end of the woods.

393
00:45:06,246 --> 00:45:09,596
I'm sure that he wasn't here by himself.

394
00:45:12,861 --> 00:45:17,123
I will give another chance
to the one who's hiding a stranger.

395
00:45:17,123 --> 00:45:19,956
Get them out of here and I won't do anything.

396
00:45:29,616 --> 00:45:30,923
Please have mercy.

397
00:45:30,923 --> 00:45:34,763
If no one confesses,
I will search every house.

398
00:45:34,763 --> 00:45:35,915
If I see them,

399
00:45:35,915 --> 00:45:39,643
I will kill them,
and the person who's hiding them.

400
00:45:39,643 --> 00:45:42,496
- Come on, search this place.
- Get up, go inside!

401
00:45:42,496 --> 00:45:43,536
Where are they?

402
00:45:43,536 --> 00:45:45,237
Go!

403
00:45:59,989 --> 00:46:01,996
I need to ask you something.

404
00:46:05,035 --> 00:46:07,094
About this ring.

405
00:46:07,094 --> 00:46:08,916
Where did you get it from?

406
00:46:10,096 --> 00:46:12,190
I don't remember.

407
00:46:12,190 --> 00:46:15,396
Can you think harder? I really want to know.

408
00:46:32,509 --> 00:46:34,430
I really don't know.

409
00:46:34,430 --> 00:46:36,131
I don't remember.

410
00:46:39,651 --> 00:46:41,950
Why are you so obsessed about this ring?

411
00:46:41,950 --> 00:46:43,651
What is going on?

412
00:46:44,339 --> 00:46:45,720
Nothing.

413
00:46:46,542 --> 00:46:48,974
I saw you holding it so tightly

414
00:46:48,974 --> 00:46:51,662
when you were unconscious
in the middle of the woods.

415
00:46:51,662 --> 00:46:54,196
It means that this must be important to you.

416
00:46:55,304 --> 00:46:59,516
If you can think of something,
it could lead to who you are.

417
00:47:00,499 --> 00:47:03,251
Therefore, just try to remember it.

418
00:47:03,251 --> 00:47:04,995
Lukjan!

419
00:47:04,995 --> 00:47:06,616
Lukjan!

420
00:47:06,616 --> 00:47:08,716
Fai and his crew are on the way.

421
00:47:10,306 --> 00:47:13,200
- You need to hide. Hurry!
- Hey!

422
00:47:13,200 --> 00:47:14,901
Who do I have to hide from?

423
00:47:27,611 --> 00:47:29,196
Search everywhere.

424
00:47:32,118 --> 00:47:33,876
What are you doing here?

425
00:47:41,182 --> 00:47:43,283
I know you're hiding them here.

426
00:47:43,283 --> 00:47:46,415
Tell me, where are you hiding them?

427
00:47:47,086 --> 00:47:48,548
Who?

428
00:47:50,989 --> 00:47:53,379
The outsiders that sneaked into Prai Island.

429
00:47:53,379 --> 00:47:55,080
Fai!

430
00:47:55,774 --> 00:47:57,475
I found this.

431
00:48:00,430 --> 00:48:01,946
What is this?

432
00:48:04,072 --> 00:48:06,846
You're going to blame me with this?

433
00:48:06,846 --> 00:48:10,760
This is a hospital, there are patients
walking in and out every day.

434
00:48:10,760 --> 00:48:12,856
How could I have hidden any outsiders?

435
00:48:15,440 --> 00:48:17,716
I don't think anybody was here.

436
00:48:19,317 --> 00:48:21,205
Did you look everywhere?

437
00:48:21,205 --> 00:48:24,076
I didn't see anyone in the back of the house.
I searched it all.

438
00:48:28,219 --> 00:48:29,920
What about Yos?

439
00:48:33,518 --> 00:48:35,096
There he is!

440
00:48:35,096 --> 00:48:36,956
Den! Come with me.

441
00:48:38,888 --> 00:48:41,116
I knew you lied to me.

442
00:48:53,296 --> 00:48:55,803
You know the rules quite well.

443
00:48:55,803 --> 00:48:58,742
People from here can't go out,
and the outsiders can come in.

444
00:48:58,742 --> 00:49:01,280
If we found them, they must die.

445
00:49:01,280 --> 00:49:02,758
Can you spare his life?

446
00:49:02,758 --> 00:49:04,756
There is no exception!

447
00:49:06,176 --> 00:49:08,336
Get over here!

448
00:49:08,336 --> 00:49:09,645
Don't you run!

449
00:49:10,619 --> 00:49:13,896
Please, don't kill him.

450
00:49:13,896 --> 00:49:16,600
He was injured,
so I took him here to treat him.

451
00:49:16,600 --> 00:49:19,342
He will be gone when he's recovered.

452
00:49:19,342 --> 00:49:22,276
Don't beg me, and shut up!

453
00:49:23,542 --> 00:49:25,893
No, I won't let you!

454
00:49:25,893 --> 00:49:28,176
I won't let anyone die like this anymore.

455
00:49:28,176 --> 00:49:29,976
This is enough!

456
00:49:29,976 --> 00:49:32,196
You're asking for it!

457
00:49:36,771 --> 00:49:38,996
You should go to hell along with this guy.

458
00:49:53,662 --> 00:49:56,756
When you were born,
your mom must have dressed you in a skirt.

459
00:49:57,972 --> 00:50:00,936
That's why you're hurting a woman
so shamelessly.

460
00:50:00,936 --> 00:50:02,716
You pussy face!

461
00:50:03,443 --> 00:50:07,116
I should feed a bullet down your throat
with a mouth like this.

462
00:50:10,435 --> 00:50:14,116
You're not just a pussy face,
but a stupid one too.

463
00:50:18,294 --> 00:50:20,316
Lukjan, come here.

464
00:51:14,910 --> 00:51:16,611
Stop!

465
00:51:19,747 --> 00:51:21,448
Dad!

466
00:51:23,395 --> 00:51:26,115
This guy is my patient.

467
00:51:26,115 --> 00:51:29,016
You can't kill him as you please.

468
00:51:29,016 --> 00:51:31,259
If I don't do anything to him,

469
00:51:31,259 --> 00:51:33,584
he won't make it out alive once Mai is back.

470
00:51:33,584 --> 00:51:35,488
You know it well,

471
00:51:35,488 --> 00:51:38,136
then why did you waste your time
treating him?

472
00:51:38,136 --> 00:51:39,934
I am a doctor.

473
00:51:39,934 --> 00:51:42,232
It's my way of healing people.

474
00:51:42,232 --> 00:51:43,933
Besides,

475
00:51:44,694 --> 00:51:47,720
you are not the boss of this place.

476
00:51:47,720 --> 00:51:50,876
When Mai is back, I will talk to him.

477
00:51:53,656 --> 00:51:55,357
Fine.

478
00:51:55,987 --> 00:51:58,741
I won't do anything to him now.

479
00:51:58,741 --> 00:52:01,664
But I don't trust him
to stay in your place like this.

480
00:52:01,664 --> 00:52:04,613
You can tie him up to the pole
in the middle of the village,

481
00:52:04,613 --> 00:52:07,520
while he is waiting for Mai's judgement.

482
00:52:07,520 --> 00:52:09,316
In the meantime,

483
00:52:10,139 --> 00:52:12,276
you can't kill him.

484
00:52:13,840 --> 00:52:15,560
Sure.

485
00:52:17,880 --> 00:52:19,581
Saeng!
